==English==

===Etymology===
Blend of ''[[w:Thomas_Bruce%2C_7th_Earl_of_Elgin|Elgin]]'' and ''[[-ism]]''; coined to describe the actions of the type carried out by [[w:Thomas_Bruce%2C_7th_Earl_of_Elgin|Thomas Bruce, 7th Earl of Elgin]] to the [[w:Elgin_Marbles|Parthenon Sculptures]] in Athens.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛlɡɪnɪzəm̩/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# An act of cultural vandalism.
# Assembly of artifacts from other countries in imperial capitals.

